Package grafioschtrader.entities

Class GTNetInstrumentSecurity

java.lang.Object
grafiosch.entities.BaseID<Integer>
grafioschtrader.entities.GTNetInstrument
grafioschtrader.entities.GTNetInstrumentSecurity
@Entity public class GTNetInstrumentSecurity extends GTNetInstrument
Instrument pool entry for securities in the GT-Network. Securities are identified by their ISIN (International Securities Identification Number) and currency, enabling cross-system matching regardless of internal IDs. This allows different Grafioschtrader instances to share price data for the same security even if they have different idSecurity values.

Usage

  • Used by GTNetLastprice for intraday price data
  • Used by GTNetHistoryquote for historical price data (foreign instruments only)
  • When GTNetInstrument.isLocalInstrument() returns true, historical data goes to Historyquote instead
See Also:
  • for base fields and local/foreign distinction
  • for currency pair instruments
